Enteral nutrition is a therapy provided routinely in the hospital, extended 
care, and home care settings for patients who are unable to maintain adequate 
oral nutrition yet have a functioning gastrointestinal tract. Information about 
the cost and effectiveness or benefits of enteral nutrition in the hospital and 
